antworld.server

Class Nest

  • java.lang.Object
    • antworld.common.NestData
      • antworld.server.Nest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Nest
extends NestData
implements java.io.Serializable
    Throwing uncaught exceptions causes the server to crash. True, it is bad to have the server crash, however these IllegalArgumentExceptions will never happen.
    So, why include them then?
    Having a function check for and throw IllegalArgumentExceptions is a way to document to future developers what the function is supposed to do (and not do).

      • calculateScore

        public void calculateScore()
        Calculates and sets the current score of this nest. Each client's goal is to maximize this value by the end of the game. The score is based on the food in this nest and the number of living ants belonging to this nest. Food carried by ants does not count towards the score.

      • getTimeOfLastMessageFromClient

        public double getTimeOfLastMessageFromClient()

      • getStatus

        public Nest.NestStatus getStatus()
        Returns:
        The status of this nest which may be:
        • EMPTY (not yet assigned to any client),
        • CONNECTED (assigned to and receiving updates from a client),
        • DISCONNECTED (assigned to a client with a dropped socket connection),
        • UNDERGROUND (assigned to a client that has been disconnected for a long time and its ants have been returned to its nest).

      • isNearNest

        public boolean isNearNest(int x,
                          int y)
        Parameters:
        x - east/west pixel (== cell) location on world map.
        y - north/south pixel (== cell) location on world map.
        Returns:
        true iff the specified location is within the yellow colored area surrounding this nest.

      • updateAutomaticAntEvents

        public void updateAutomaticAntEvents()
        Update automatic ant events of all ants in this nest. Automatic events include:
        1. Attrition damage.
        2. Removing ants that died last tick from ant sets.
        3. Decrementing move/busy time.
        4. Changing last turn's actions to default NOOP

      • updateReceivePacket

        public void updateReceivePacket(AntWorld world)
        Applies client ant action requests. Note: no changes in this loop are made to ants belonging to a client that the client does not include in their return package nor for which a valid action is not provided.

        world -
